@node HELP_SYSTEM "A_Sweeper.Guide : System requirements"

@{b}Hardware :@{ub}

A_Sweeper has been written to run on AGA machines, or at least, using an 8 color workbench.
A_Sweeper needs some Ko on your disk and in memory. It is not small, because the program includes some binary graphics and sounds data but it should not take more than 115 Ko.


@{b}Logiciel :@{ub}

To run A_Sweeper your Amiga must have two standards libraries in the 'Libs:' drawer, the GadTools.library, and the Locale.library.

Your WorkBench must be set with at least 8 colors.
Ready to run with MagicWorkbench palette, A_Sweeper can be used with all the palettes you want. Just use the @{" Personnalisation" link HELP_PERSON}.


@endnode


