@node HELP_INSTAL "A_Sweeper.Guide : Hard disk installation"

@{b}Installation :@{ub}

A_Sweeper installation should not be a problem.

The easiest way, is to drag the drawer icon on the floppy to the drawer on your harddisk where you want A_Sweeper to be installed.

For those who want to use Installer, a script exists. Just double-clic on the installation icon and follow the instructions.


@{b}Removing A_Sweeper from your Harddisk :@{ub}

Just remove the A_Sweeper drawer, all objects used are there. It's simple, quick and clean. 


@endnode


@node HELP_REGLES "A_Sweeper.guide : Game rules"

@{i}Basis :@{ui}

  The one who knows Windows and its Sweeper 'WinMine' don't need any explanations. For the others here are the rules and goal.

  You first get a grid with 10 columns and 10 rows (this is the default).
  This makes 100 cells where the program will hide a fixed number of mines (default is 10).
  The goal is to find where the mines are, without exploding !
  First click on a cell. A_Sweeper will immediately inform you of the result, by displaying its attributes. The possible informations are :
        - Empty cell : the cell isn't a mine and none of the neighbour
          cells is a mine.
        - Number x  : the cell isn't a mine, but x of the neighbour cells
          is (are) explosive(s).
        - Mine      : Bad luck, you exploded. Game ends.

  You have some help !
  For example, if you think a cell is a mine, you can mark it by clicking with the right mouse button. A small flag will appear there. If you click one more time on this cell with the right button, the flag will be replaced by a "?" indicating a doubt. A third pression with the right button will place the cell in the normal 'unclicked' state.

  For those who like challenges, a timer will allow them to make some competitions.

  To stop a game running, click on 'Stop'. To exit click on the window close gadget.
  To start a game, click on 'start'.
  The 'pause' gagdet allows you to stop the running game, without ending it. It's useful when phone rings, etc ... Some ones use it to cheat in some speed competitions. Well, some always need to ...
  You can only use menus when game is stopped or paused, because the right mouse button has a special meaning in A_Sweeper.

@endnode


@node HELP_PARAMS "A_Sweeper.Guide : Settings options"

You can act on six settings.

    1) @{u}@{FG shine}Number of rows in the grid :@{FG text}@{uu}
        Clic in this gadget and type in the number of desired rows.

    2) @{u}@{FG shine}Number of columns in the grid :@{FG text}@{uu}
        Clic in this gadget and type in the number of desired columns.  

    3) @{u}@{FG shine}Number of mines to discover :@{FG text}@{uu}
        Clic in this gagdet and type in the number of mines that will be
        hidden in the grid. 

    4) @{u}@{FG shine}Sound effects (On/Off) :@{FG text}@{uu}
        Set the checkmark for this cell if you want sound effects when the
        game ends. If you don't want any sounds remove the checkmark.

    5) @{u}@{FG shine}Save Hi-Scores (Yes/No) :@{FG text}@{uu}
        Set the checkmark for this cell if you want to save the best times.
        If you don't like speed contests remove the checkmark.

    6) @{u}@{FG shine}Drawer where the icons can be found :@{FG text}@{uu}
        This setting allows you to change the aspect of the different cells
        of the grid. Just indicate the drawer where the icons to use are.
        A_Sweeper comes with at least four drawers to be used with MagicWb
        and NewIcons, for 1x1 screens (ex : DoublePal), and for 2x1 screens
        (ex : PAL).
        Note that to choose a drawer you must click on the 'drawer' icon. A
        path requester will appear and let you select the one you want.

When the settings have been modified, press on the appropriate button.
The choices are :               

    @{"Save    " link HELP_PARAMS_BOUTONS}

    @{"Use     " link HELP_PARAMS_BOUTONS}

    @{"Cancel  " link HELP_PARAMS_BOUTONS}

@endnode


@node HELP_PARAMS_BOUTONS "A_Sweeper.Guide : Settings, buttons"

@{u}@{FG shine}Save     :@{FG text}@{uu}
If after changing settings, you want to use them, and save them to disk as 'default' settings,press this gadget.

@{u}@{FG shine}Utiliser :@{FG text}@{uu}
If after changing settings, you want to use them, but not save them to disk as 'default' settings,press this gadget.

@{u}@{FG shine}Annuler  :@{FG text}@{uu}
If after changing settings, you don't want to use them, press this gadget.

@endnode


@node HELP_PERSON "A_Sweeper.Guide : Personnalisation"

    A_sweeper was written to allow you to change the aspect of any type of cell. There are thirteen icons used. You just need to draw new ones, and to change the 'drawer' setting to get a new A_Swepper screen. At least four drawers to use with MagicWorkbench and NewIcons come with A_Sweeper. For screens in DoublePal (or equivalent) and for screens in PAL (or equivalent).

    Here are the icons, the program needs :

        - 1_Mine.iff : Unmined cell. 1 neighbour  is  a mine.
        - 2_Mine.iff : Unmined cell. 2 neighbours are   mines.
        - 3_Mine.iff : Unmined cell. 3 neighbours are   mines.
        - 4_Mine.iff : Unmined cell. 4 neighbours are   mines.
        - 5_Mine.iff : Unmined cell. 5 neighbours are   mines.
        - 6_Mine.iff : Unmined cell. 6 neighbours are   mines.
        - 7_Mine.iff : Unmined cell. 7 neighbours are   mines.
        - 8_Mine.iff : Unmined cell. 8 neighbours are   mines.
        - Clickd.iff : This cell was clicked, isn't a mine, and no neighbour cell is a mine.
        - Flaged.iff : This is supposed to be a mine (flaged).
        - Mined!.iff : Oops, it's a mine.
        - QuestM.iff : What the hell is this cell ? not sure (?).
        - UnClic.iff : Unclicked cell.

    Unlike the previous version, your icons can have as many colours as you want.

    If you make some very beautiful icons, think to me ...
    Good drawing !

@endnode


@node HELP_HISTOR "A_Sweeper.Guide : History"

